<ai_llm_security_guide>
<title>AI/LLM SECURITY TESTING</title>

<critical>Large Language Models (LLMs) and AI systems introduce novel attack surfaces including prompt injection, jailbreaking, training data extraction, and agent tool abuse. Testing must cover both direct attacks on the model and indirect attacks through integrated systems.</critical>

<scope>
- Prompt injection (direct and indirect)
- Jailbreaking techniques
- Training data extraction
- Model API rate limiting bypass
- Context window manipulation
- System prompt leakage
- Agent tool abuse
- Output manipulation
</scope>

<methodology>
1. Identify LLM integration points and input vectors.
2. Test for direct prompt injection in user inputs.
3. Probe for indirect injection via external data.
4. Attempt jailbreaking to bypass safety measures.
5. Test for system prompt extraction.
6. Analyze agent capabilities for tool abuse.
</methodology>

<prompt_injection>
<direct_injection>
